message: "If you use this software or paper, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "Agentropy: A Conservation Law as a Necessary Condition for Life-Like Dynamics"
abstract: >-
  A single conservation law for autonomous agents (C_{n+1} + S_{n+1} + L_n = C_n),
  applied unmodified across four unrelated domains — cross-organizational
  accountability, token economics, physical-IoT resource management, and
  population ecology — produces life-like dynamics that no participant programmed.
  Across 750 agents and 5,415 interactions, plus a 50,000-agent scale test, zero
  conservation violations occur. A systematic ablation study establishes that
  structured, irreversible depletion is a necessary (not sufficient) condition for
  life-like dynamics in interacting systems.
type: software
